1) uname : print system information
    Option: -a: all system info
    Example: uname -a (Displays all sys info)

2) whoami : Display current username

3) df : Show disk usage
    Option: -h (Human readable sizes)
    Example: df -h

4) du : Estimate file and dir sizes
    Options:
      -h : human readable size
      -s : total size only
    Example: du -sh dir1/ (Provides the total size of the specified dir)

5) free : Display memory usage info 
    Options: -h : human readable sizes
    Example: free -h (Displays memory usage in human-readable format)

6) uptime : show system uptime 

7) lscpu : display CPU information

8) lspci : list PCI devices

9) lsusb : lists all the connected USB devices
